❤️ Hi friends!

Top news of the hour:

▪️ Overnight, Russian air defence shot down 14 Ukrainian drones: 12 over the Kursk region, one over the Belgorod region and one over the Voronezh region, the Russia’s Defence ministry reported;

▪️The Ukrainian air defence shot down 30 of 38 Russia's attack drones overnight, the Ukrainian Air Force claimed; the local administrations reported damage from Russian air attacks in the Sumy and Chernigov regions;

▪️More than 11,000 people left the Krasnoyaruzhsky district of the Russia’s Belgorod region due to the operational situation, the local authorities reported;

▪️Washington plans to launch a powerful information campaign to discredit Zelensky in order to force him to leave his post, Russia’s Foreign Intelligence Service (SVR) reported;

▪️ The US administration wants to install  Arsen Avakov as Zelensky’s successor; the former Minister of Internal Affairs of Ukraine is viewed favourably in Washington due to his "close ties with Ukrainian nationalist formations and his continuing contacts with European leaders", the SVR added;

▪️The draft age in Ukraine should be from 20 to 50 years, said Ukrainian MP Kostenko from the Golos party.

@ukraine_watch

Air defense forces shot down 24 out of 29 Shahed drones launched across Ukraine overnight.

The drones were shot down in Kherson, Odesa, Mykolaiv, Poltava, Sumy, Dnipro, Kyiv, Vinnytsia, and Zhytomyr regions.

@liveukraine_media

❤️ Hi friends!

Top news of the hour:

▪️ Sevastopol, Crimea, was shelled at night by ATACMS missiles with a cluster munition. Traffic in the city was partially blocked. There is no information on casualties;

▪️ Russian forces attacked facilities in Pavlograd, Krivoy Rog, Kirovograd, Kropivnitsky, Zaporozhye and an airfield in the Nikolayev region last night;

▪️ Russian air defence forces destroyed two Ukrainian UAVs over the Kursk region last night, while four other UAVs were intercepted over the Krasnodar region, the Russian Defence Ministry said.

@ukraine_watch
